mary entry point. It:\\n- Loads API keys from `/root/.hermes/.env`\\n- Reads the full voice profile\\n- Injects it as mandatory context before any task prompt\\n- Spawns Apollo via `hermes chat --non-interactive`\\n\\n## Privacy\\n\\n**Private — never share outside this system:**\\n\\n```\\n/root/.hermes/profiles/apollo/apollo-voice-profile.md\\n/root/.hermes/skills/invoke-apollo/scripts/invoke-apollo.sh\\n```\\n\\nThese files are excluded from all git operations. Do not commit, push, or otherwise expose them.\\n\\n## Usage\\n\\n### Via Hermes delegation\\nWhen another agent needs Apollo to write something:\\n```\\nUse the invoke-apollo skill. Task: [describe the writing task]\\n```\\n\\n### Via terminal\\n```bash\\ninvoke-apollo \\\"Write a short essay on ETHis 2026\\\"\\n# or\\nhermes skills run invoke-apollo --task \\\"Write a tweet about ETHis\\\"\\n```\\n\\n### Via cron\\nSchedule Apollo writing tasks that always include voice context:\\n```bash\\nhermes cron create \\\"0 9 * * *\\\" \\\\\\n  --prompt \\\"Use invoke-apollo. Task: Morning reflection — 3 paragraphs on the state of the ETHis project.\\\" \\\\\\n  --delivery telegram\\n```\\n\\n## Prompt Injection Template\\n\\nThe skill injects voice context using this exact pattern:\\n\\n```\\n[VOICE PROFILE — MANDATORY CONTEXT. Read this before writing anything.]\\n<full apollo-voice-profile.md content>\\n\\n[TASK]\\n<user task description>\\n\\nFollow the voice profile above exactly. Write in Donny Lewis's voice — not generic AI voice.\\nStart in the particular, arrive at the universal. No jargon. No hype. No crypto Twitter.\\n```\\n\\n## Voice Profile Key Points (for reference)\\n\\n- **Structure**: concrete → universal (never the reverse)\\n- **Rhythm**: accumulating sentences + short declarative landing beats\\n- **Tone**: warm, direct, slightly formal, never flashy\\n- **Humor**: dry, self-aware, parenthetical — never at someone's expense\\n- **Endings**: quiet, at ground level — never a drumbeat conclusion