kills\": [], \"content\": \"---\\nname: invoke-apollo\\ndescription: Delegates writing tasks to Apollo while automatically injecting Donny Lewis's voice profile as mandatory context. Use this whenever a writing task should be in Donny's voice and tone. Works when called by Aphrodite, Hermes, Hephaestus, or directly. Apollo always receives the full voice profile before any writing task.\\nversion: 1.1.0\\nauthor: Donny Lewis / DVS\\nlicense: private\\nmetadata:\\n  dvs:\\n    tags: [apollo, delegation, writing, voice, Donny-Lewis]\\n    voice_profile_path: /root/.hermes/profiles/apollo/apollo-voice-profile.md\\n    privacy_note: Voice profile is private. Never push to GitHub or share outside this system.\\n---\\n\\n# invoke-apollo v1.1.0\\n\\nA Hermes skill that bridges voice memory across subagent isolation. When you delegate a writing task to Apollo, this skill automatically reads Donny's voice profile and injects it as mandatory context — so Apollo always writes in Donny's voice even when spawned by other agents (Hermes, Athena, Aphrodite, Hephaestus, etc.).\\n\\n## The Problem It Solves\\n\\nWhen Hermes delegates to Apollo via `delegate_task`, Apollo runs in a fresh session without the voice profile. This meant Apollo's output was generic AI voice — correct structure, wrong tone. v1.1.0 fixes this at the skill layer, before Apollo is ever spawned.\\n\\n## How It Works\\n\\n1. **Reads** `/root/.hermes/profiles/apollo/apollo-voice-profile.md` (Donny's full 241-line voice memory)\\n2. **Prepends** the entire voice profile as `[VOICE PROFILE — MANDATORY CONTEXT]` before the task\\n3. **Spawns** Apollo directly via `hermes chat` with the combined prompt (bypassing `delegate_task` isolation)\\n4. Apollo writes with full voice memory — no drift, no generic AI tone\\n\\n## Entry Point\\n\\n```\\n/root/.hermes/skills/invoke-apollo/scripts/invoke-apollo.sh\\n```\\n\\nThis is the primary entry point. It:\\n- Loads API keys from `/root/.hermes/.env`\\n- Reads the full voice 