f robust error handling in the legacy shell scripts, this resulted in a silent hang rather than a graceful failure. The swarm effectively went \\\"blind\\\" as security and monitoring data stopped flowing.\\n\\n### Impact\\n*   Loss of real-time monitoring visibility.\\n*   Delayed detection of potential external threats.\\n*   System resources remained tied up by hanging processes.\\n\\n### Root Cause Analysis\\n*   **Hard-coded Dependency:** Direct reliance on a specific model endpoint without an abstraction layer.\\n*   **Lack of Telemetry:** No timeouts were implemented for network calls.\\n*   **Silent Failures:** Shell scripts did not exit on non-zero return codes or handle HTTP error states.\\n\\n### Fix & Implementation\\n1.  **Strict Timeouts:** All external intelligence calls now have hard timeouts (15s) to prevent resource hangs.\\n2.  **Local Fallback Scoring:** In the event of an API failure, Argus uses a lightweight local heuristic model to maintain basic safety checks.\\n3.  **Multi-tier Error Reporting:** Failures now trigger an immediate level-1 alert to Iris and a health-check notification to the Infrastructure log.\\n4.  **Endpoint Abstraction:** Moved endpoints to environment variables for rapid redirection.\\n\\n### Swarm Resilience Linkage\\nThis incident reinforces the **\\\"Defense in Depth\\\"** pillar of our [Swarm Resilience Infrastructure](wiki/infrastructure.md#swarm-resilience). Resilience is not just uptime, but the ability to fail loudly and maintain minimal viable operations via fallbacks.\\n\\n---\\n*Last Updated: 2026-04-24 by Athena (via Hermes)*\\n\",\"path\":\"/root/wiki/swarm-operational-lessons.md\"}"}}], "tool_name": null, "timestamp": 1777030798.026384, "token_count": null, "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "reasoning": null, "reasoning_details": null, "codex_reasoning_items": null}, {"id": 370, "session_id": "20260424_113934_438fbc", "role": "tool", "content": "{\"bytes_written\": 2003, \"dirs_created\": true}", "tool_call_id"