"\\n- Include the wiki path when relevant: /root/workspace/my-wiki\\n- If the task has a deliverable, name it: \\\"Write the result to wiki/agent-build-order.md\\\"\\n- For multi-step tasks, break into sequential athena calls rather than one compound prompt\\n\\n### Capturing Output\\n- Athena's response is printed to stdout — capture it if needed: output=$(athena chat -q '...')\\n- For long research tasks, pipe output to a file: athena chat -q '...' > /tmp/athena-output.md\\n- Athena will report every file it creates or updates — parse this to confirm the task is done\\n\\n## Example\\n\\nTask: User asks Hermes to update the wiki with a new X post about an agent dependency.\\n\\nHermes runs:\\n  athena chat -q 'Ingest the following X post into the DVS wiki and update wiki/agent-build-order.md with any new dependency information. Post content: \\\"@51bodila AgentX depends on AgentB and AgentC before it can be deployed.\\\" Wiki path: /root/workspace/my-wiki'\\n\\nAthena responds with a summary of changes made and files updated.\\n\\nSecond example — wiki query:\\n  athena chat -q 'Query the DVS wiki at /root/workspace/my-wiki and tell me everything known about the @51bodila agent dependency graph and build order'\\n\\n## Don'ts\\n- Do not call athena for tasks that are pure code execution, system administration, or file manipulation — those belong in Hermes terminal/file tools\\n- Do not pass sensitive information (API keys, tokens, credentials) in the task prompt — Athena logs inputs\\n- Do not send underspecified prompts like \\\"research something\\\" — Athena cannot ask follow-up questions mid-run\\n- Do not assume Athena remembers prior Hermes conversations — every call is a fresh session; always include full context\\n- Do not delegate creative writing (screenplays, poems, personal writing) to Athena — that is Donny's domain and Athena will not modify it\\n\", \"path\": \"delegate-to-athena/SKILL.md\", \"skill_dir\": \"/root/.hermes/skills/delegate-to-athena\"